data.name: Breakfast Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A delicious breakfast twist on a classic burger, featuring a juicy patty topped with a perfectly fried egg and melted cheese.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat a skillet over medium heat and add olive oil.
Form ground beef into two patties, season with salt, black pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder.
Cook the beef patties in the skillet for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until they reach your desired doneness.
In the last minute of cooking, place cheese slices on top of the patties to melt.
While the patties are cooking, heat another small pan over medium heat and fry the eggs to your preference (sunny side up or over easy).
Toast the burger buns lightly in the same skillet or a toaster.
Assemble your burger: on the bottom bun, layer spinach, the beef patty with melted cheese, a fried egg, sliced avocado, and tomato. Top with the other half of the bun.
data.detailedName: Breakfast Burger with Fried Egg and Avocado
data.modifiersForBase: Breakfast twist with egg and avocado
